how to write commands in terminal for activating the env (to add env in vs code)

1. Open folder in vs code that locatte your code folder
2. in terminal make sure your code folder is in pythonPath
3. then , type "activate yourenvname"

if error occurs unauthorized
run this

Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser

then, activate yourenvname
 
now it works.